Some patients had dyspnoea and/or hypoxaemia one week after the onset of the disease.
As regards serious cases, patients rapidly developed acute respiratory syndrome, septic shock, metabolic acidosis, and coagulopathy.
Patients with fever and/or respiratory symptoms as well as those with acute fever, even in the absence of thoracic radiographic anomalies, should be tested for the virus in order to allow an early diagnosis.
