The epidemic disrupted the organisation of the 2020 Summer Olympics, which was initially due to begin at the end of July; the International Olympic Committee announced on 24 March that the event would be "replanned beyond 2020, but not later than summer 2021". The casinos and other gaming facilities around the world closed and the live poker tournaments were either postponed or cancelled.
