Some medical procedures such as intubation and cardiopulmonary re-animation (RCP) can spread respiratory secretions and therefore lead to air propagation.
Although there are concerns about the spread of seals, this risk is perceived to be low. The virus is the most contagious when people have symptoms; although the spread may be possible before symptoms appear, the risk is low.
